COMP2156 DevOps Course
In this course, students delve into DevOps practices, mastering protocols and best practices to boost workplace productivity. They gain hands-on experience with industry-standard tools like Ansible and Git, while exploring data formats such as XML, JSON, YAML, and YANG for network automation. By course end, students are adept at implementing CI/CD, leveraging cloud database technologies, and automating application configurations. They also excel in VCS workflows, architectural decisions, code monitoring, and security integration, empowering them to optimize DevOps processes effectively.